VERDICT: confirmed-but-no-uca
REASON: Both halves of the oracle reproduce on HEAD. Primary claim: src/mmu.rs:240-256 region_align_decide is #[verifier::external_body] with ensures only constraining aligned_addr<=addr and addr_offset=addr-aligned_addr (lines 244-246); the stronger invariant align_result_valid_spec at lines 226-231 (coverage: aligned_addr+aligned_size >= addr+size, plus aligned_size>0) is orphaned — grep confirms it is not referenced in any ensures clause across the module. Verus witness: add `result.aligned_size as int % align as int == 0` to the ensures and verification fails on the clamp branch (line 254). PoC: region_align_decide(1, u32::MAX-1, 0x8000_0000) — precondition addr+size = u32::MAX satisfied — computes raw = ((u32::MAX-1)+1+0x8000_0000-1)/0x8000_0000*0x8000_0000 = 2*0x8000_0000 = 0x1_0000_0000 > u32::MAX, hits the silent clamp and returns aligned_size = 0xFFFF_FFFF with 0xFFFF_FFFF % 0x8000_0000 = 0x7FFF_FFFF ≠ 0, violating the MM4 claim in the module docstring lines 22-26 ("region alignment preserves page alignment and no overflow"). The result is consumed unchecked by zephyr/gale_mmu.c:120-136 gale_k_mem_region_align and written back into Zephyr's out-parameters, so downstream page-table sizing sees a non-align-multiple. Secondary claim: src/mmu.rs:347-360 validate_unmap_request only enforces addr>=page_size (before-guard) and size+2*page_size<=u32::MAX (via validate_guard_total) but never checks addr+size+page_size<=u32::MAX; PoC validate_unmap_request(0xFFFF_F000, 0x1000, 0x1000) returns true yet the trailing-guard end = 0x1_0000_1000 wraps past u32::MAX, so the "after" guard page aliases [0, 0x1000). Interestingness: not a documented caller-responsibility precondition (the precondition addr+size<=u32::MAX does not bound `align`, and MM4/MM8 are advertised unconditionally in the header); not a hardware-config issue (align and addr are runtime-supplied from Zephyr); not a known limitation (artifacts/stpa.yaml §"Analysis scope" explicitly excludes UCAs; no safety/stpa/ucas.yaml exists; SC-6 in stpa.yaml covers arithmetic overflow abstractly but no MMU-specific hazard or constraint exists). No existing UCA fits. Recommend filing a new UCA-MMU-1 ("region_align_decide returns an AlignResult whose aligned_size is not a multiple of align or under-covers the requested range because the ROUND_UP overflow is silently clamped to u32::MAX, and the module ensures clause fails to prove MM4 coverage/alignment") feeding a new MMU hazard (analogue of H-6 but in the address-arithmetic direction; leads to L-1/L-2), plus a sibling UCA-MMU-2 ("validate_unmap_request accepts addr+size+page_size that wraps u32::MAX, letting the trailing-guard page alias low memory"). Both belong under a future "Memory management" hazard grouping; neither can be grouped under SC-6 because that constraint is about the use of checked_* ops, not about the ensures-spec completeness gap shown here.
